pmacct (Promiscuous mode IP Accounting package)
pmacct is Copyright (C) 2003-2005 by Paolo Lucente

pmacctd		pcap-based accounting daemon; it gathers packets from an
		interface it is bound to (enabling optionally Promiscuous
		mode); statistics may be either pushed to stdout, stored
		in a memory table or a PostgreSQL/MySQL database.
nfacctd		NetFlow accounting daemon; listens for NetFlow v1/v5/v9
		packets on one or more interfaces; statistics may be either
		pushed to stdout, stored in a memory table or a PostgreSQL/
		MySQL database.
pmacct  	commandline pmacct client; used to retrieve data from an
		active memroy plugin; it may ask for specific entries or
		perform a bulk data retrieval; output may be text-formatted
		or counters-only, suitable for data injection in tools like
		MRTG, RRDtool, SNMP server or Gnuplot. 
pmmyplay	pmacct MySQL logfile player; it is able to play logfiles,
		previously produced by a SQL plugin, connecting to a MySQL
		server.
pmpgplay	pmacct PostgreSQL logfile player; it is able to play logfiles,
		previously produced by a SQL plugin, connecting to a PostgreSQL
		server.

